<TITLE> New trust fund at DU launched </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 3 (bdnews24.com)  A programme on Saturday marked the launch of a trust fund for the Department of International Relations (IR) of Dhaka University. "Syed Imtiaz Ahmed Trust Fund" was named after the late assistant professor of the department who died from heart disease on 2006. The department's chair, professor Ruksana Kibria, handed over a cheque of Tk 4 lakh to the university's treasurer professor Mizanur Rahman, on behalf of Dr Nepisha Begum, mother of the late teacher. The fund targets to provide scholarships to the meritorious students of the department every year. The programme was attended by vice chancellor professor A A M S Arefin Siddique, registrar (acting) Syed Rezaur Rahman, professor of IR department Mohammed Ramjul Haq, wife of the late teacher Lailufar Yasmin and others. He was the youngest son of late Ahmed Humayun, editor of Dainik Bangla. bd
